## 1. Output Specification

- **Deliverable:** A polished, print-ready **PDF** hosted on GitHub Pages (viewed/downloaded from the repo, same hosting approach as the NN Finance Handbook).
- **Recommended workflow:** Build as a single-file **HTML page in the Handbook design system** (§8), then export to PDF via print-to-PDF with `@media print` styles (page breaks between major sections, no sticky nav, US Letter). This keeps visual parity with the handbook while producing a clean PDF.
- **Length target:** ~10–16 pages.
- **Page furniture:** Cover page → Bismillah SVG → table of contents → numbered sections (01, 02, 03… matching handbook convention) → closing/footer: "Young Muslims · Finance Department · finance@ymsisters.com · Q2 FY2026 National Finance Report · For Internal Use Only".
- **Reporting period:** Q2 FY2026 (specify exact months: `[CONFIRM: e.g., April–June 2026]`).

## 2. Audience & Tone

- **Audience:** YM National Shura (NS), SubRegional Coordinators (SRCs), SR Finance Leads, NN Coordinators (NNCs) across 170+ chapters, and national leadership.
- **Tone:** Professional but warm and community-oriented. Celebrate wins, be transparent about numbers, be firm-but-friendly on policy reminders. Mirror the handbook's voice: direct rules ("No Receipt = No Approval") softened with helpful explanation.
- **Islamic framing:** Open with Bismillah (use the handbook's `bismillah.svg`). Honorifics: Allah ﷻ, the Messenger ﷺ. Appropriate du'a/gratitude framing in intro and closing is welcome; keep it natural, not decorative filler.

## 3. Glossary / Terminology (use consistently)

| Term | Meaning |
|---|---|
| YM | Young Muslims (the national organization; this is the Sisters' finance report) |
| NN | NeighborNet — a local chapter |
| SR | SubRegion — a grouping of NNs |
| NS | National Shura — national leadership council |
| NNC | NeighborNet Coordinator |
| SRC | SubRegional Coordinator |
| YMC | YM Conference — national conference, held in Baltimore |
| YMLC | YM Leadership Conference — held in Florida this year; event occurs in Q3 but **finances hit in Q2** |
| MAD | Muslim Advocacy Day — advocacy event in Washington, D.C. |
| YM Gives | National service campaign run across chapters |
| JotForm | The single intake form for all income/expense/transfer submissions |
| Dashboard | Per-NN/SR finance dashboard spreadsheets refreshed from JotForm data |
| YM Bank | Chapter funds held at YM National (not physically with the NN) |
| Cash Box | NN's local physical cash (≤ $200 at any time) |
| Personal Bank | NNC's personal account temporarily holding YM funds |

