### 5.8 Notes from Finance
**Handbook launch (lead item, celebratory):** Announce the release of the **NN Finance Handbook** — link to https://sulphia-iqbal.github.io/neighbornet-finances-handbook/ym-nn-finances-handbook.html. One-paragraph description: covers accounts, JotForm submission types, dashboards, approvals, lump sums, audits, with a full case study.

**Friendly Financial Policy Reminders** (card list, firm-but-friendly tone):
1. **Zelle is now available for reimbursements.** Prefer **Zelle over Venmo** when possible. Coordinate Zelle details with finance@ymsisters.com after submitting the JotForm.
2. **No personal expenses on the same receipt as YM expenses.** Mixed receipts **will be denied** — we are strict on this. Make YM purchases on their own receipt.
3. **Proper event names in Expense Details are required.** Format: `Date · Event Name · Subcategory` (e.g., `1/9/26 NJ Gala – Decorations`). Some NNs are omitting event names and being contacted individually to explain their expenses — save everyone the back-and-forth by labeling correctly the first time.
4. **NN collab confusion, cleared up:** When two NNs split costs, up to **3 JotForms** are needed — (①) the payer's reimbursement expense, (②) the other NN's expense for sending their share, (③) the receiving NN's income. Point readers to Handbook §05b for the full worked example.
- Optional additions if space allows: receipt format rules (PDFs not screenshots for online orders), "no receipt = no approval."

